<br>
Code:<br>
<br>
When entity1 (pet) swings at entity2 (NPC)<br>
<br>
if (entity1 == pet &amp;&amp; state(entity2) == mezzed)<br>
    fail and return 'cannot hit/asleep';<br>
<br>
calc hits here.<br>
<br>
How hard is that? Given multiprocessor servers, spinlock the state check of Entity2 (only one action can ever happen on a 'multithread locked' bit of data), and viola, instant gratification and SOLID design forbidding any pet from breaking mez. Efficiency drops only a little for situations where it's a PC checking (but has to be done anyways) or when a pet hits a lot (passes first check, checks second regularly).<br>
<br>
Alternatively,<br>
<br>
In Mez code:<br>
<br>
Iterate through mob's hate list (anyone who attacked it)<br>
    Send message/event to entity &quot;I am mezzed&quot;<br>
<br>
Next action sequence by pet, interprets 'I am mezzed' event. Wipes said mob from hate list, reports to master &quot;I cannot wake.&quot;<br>
<br>
So... that said, either there is a coded 'chance for pet to go nuts', or it's a bug. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 8:44:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=973.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet breaking mezzes</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As for DoT's, yes the person who cast the DoT is shown as breaking mez.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
